description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse Band 5 - Stroke Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Salford Royal Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic nurse to join the Hyperacute stroke unit on a fixed term contract of 3 months. The Hyperacute Stroke Unit at Salford Royal caters for patients who have experienced a Stroke throughout the Greater Manchester area. The unit has a fast turn over and there is the opportunity to learn and develop new enhanced skills working as part of a multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Registered Nurse would be trained in IV therapy, clinical and neurological observations, blood glucose monitoring, care of the acutely unwell adult and venipuncture and cannulation would be a desirable. There is the opportunity for some training on the job. You should have excellent communication skills as this role is key working within a big team providing a high standard of care to patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Patterns: pattern is 0700-19.30pm or 19.00pm-07.30am &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Day Rate - &lt;strong&gt;£13.79 per hour &lt;/strong&gt;Night/Sat Rate - £&lt;strong&gt;17.93per hour Band 6- £22.07 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working within the Nursing and Midwifery guidelines, you will work under the direction and supervision of the team leader to provide care to patients with complex and non-complex needs with the aim of promoting independence and self-management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to apply for this post you &lt;strong&gt;must&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have a minimum of 6 months experience in a similar role held within the last 2 years&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have a full clean driving license&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have good communication skills and demonstrate evidence of team working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be able to take direction and instruction and be honest and trustworthy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, caring and reliable service you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- competitive, weekly pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- first choice of available bank shifts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- access to 24 hour service centre and online booking portal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- access to the NHSP Stakeholder Pension- paid annual leave, statutory maternity and paternity pay (subject to qualifying criteria)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- training and development opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- A flexible way of working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
